Root Cause Analysis

The Apache service was correctly configured and actively listening on port 6400.

However, the Linux firewall (iptables) denied all incoming traffic that did not explicitly match an ACCEPT rule.

Since no rule existed for TCP port 6400, every connection attempt was rejected before reaching the Apache service.

Adding an ACCEPT rule for port 6400 restored remote access while maintaining the existing firewall policy.

