Key Takeaways
A running service does not always mean it is reachable.
The error message "No route to host" can indicate firewall rules blocking traffic, not only routing issues.
Always verify each layer of troubleshooting:
Service status
Service configuration
Listening ports
Local connectivity
Remote connectivity
Firewall policies
Linux firewall rules are processed in order, making rule placement critical.
A structured troubleshooting process helps identify root causes efficiently without making unnecessary configuration changes.
