💡 Reflection

This lab reinforced an important DevOps principle: effective troubleshooting starts with narrowing down the problem layer by layer. Although the initial symptoms suggested an Apache issue, 
the real cause was an iptables rule rejecting inbound traffic. By validating the service, configuration, listening ports, and finally the firewall, I was able to resolve the issue without 
compromising the server's security. This exercise strengthened my confidence in diagnosing Linux network service problems using a methodical, evidence-driven approach.
